Let the radius of the smaller circle be $r$; then the radius of the larger circle is $4r$.  The area of the gray region is the area of the larger circle minus the area of the smaller circle.  The area of a circle with radius $r$ is $\pi r^2$, so the area of the gray region is \begin{align*}
\pi (4r)^2 - \pi r^2 &= 16 \pi r^2 - \pi r^2 \\
&= \boxed{15 \pi} \text{ square units}.
\end{align*}

